module terok_socket 1.1;

# Targeted SELinux policy for terok service sockets.
#
# Defines ``terok_socket_t`` ŌĆö a custom type that terok host services
# apply to their Unix sockets via ``setsockcreatecon()`` so that
# rootless Podman containers (``container_t``) can connect *without*
# granting container_t broad connectto on unconfined_t sockets.
#
# Three narrowly scoped rules:
#
# 1. ``unconfined_t`` (the typical Fedora workstation user + their
#    systemd --user services) may create/bind/listen/accept/IO on
#    ``terok_socket_t`` sockets, and may ``connectto`` them as a host-
#    side client (the ``terok`` CLI itself, ``terok sickbay``, auth
#    tooling, etc.).  This covers the lean-mode target environment.
#    Confined-user setups (``user_t``, ``staff_t``, ``sysadm_t``) are
#    *not* covered and must add their own rules.
#
# 2. ``container_runtime_t`` ŌĆö the per-container supervisor is spawned
#    by terok-sandbox's OCI hook, which crun runs in its own domain, so
#    the supervisor that binds the vault / ssh-signer / gate / clearance
#    sockets inherits ``container_runtime_t`` rather than the operator's
#    ``unconfined_t``.  It needs the same create/bind/listen/IO set to
#    stand those listeners up.  Granting it to the whole runtime domain
#    is broader than a dedicated supervisor type would be, but the
#    integrity property still holds: ``container_t`` (rule 3) can only
#    ``connectto``, never ``create``, so a sandboxed agent still cannot
#    forge a ``terok_socket_t`` listener to phish a sibling's tokens ŌĆö
#    and ``container_runtime_t`` is already in the TCB for every
#    container it launches.  A dedicated ``terok_supervisor_t`` (via a
#    type transition) is a possible future tightening.
#
# 3. ``container_t`` (rootless Podman containers) may ``connectto`` ŌĆö
#    and only ``connectto`` ŌĆö ``terok_socket_t`` sockets.  This is
#    the exception we carve out of the default SELinux rule that
#    blocks ``container_t ŌåÆ non-container-socket connectto``.
#    Containers cannot create new ``terok_socket_t`` sockets, so a
#    compromised container cannot set up a malicious listener that
#    wears this label.
#
# Written in checkmodule-native module syntax (no refpolicy ``m4``
# macros), so the build path is ``checkmodule -M -m`` ŌåÆ
# ``semodule_package`` ŌåÆ ``semodule -i``.
#
# Install:  sudo bash install_policy.sh
# Remove:   sudo semodule -r terok_socket

require {
    type container_t;
    type container_runtime_t;
    type unconfined_t;
    class unix_stream_socket {
        create bind listen accept
        read write getattr getopt setopt shutdown
        connectto
    };
}

type terok_socket_t;

allow unconfined_t terok_socket_t:unix_stream_socket {
    create bind listen accept
    read write getattr getopt setopt shutdown
    connectto
};

allow container_runtime_t terok_socket_t:unix_stream_socket {
    create bind listen accept
    read write getattr getopt setopt shutdown
    connectto
};

allow container_t terok_socket_t:unix_stream_socket connectto;
